This issue has not been addressed at the ninth summit initiated yesterday in Marseille.
French President Nicolas Sarkozy, EU President-in-Office, José Manuel Barroso, President of the Commission and Javier Solana, Senior Representative for Foreign Policy, received Manmohan Singh, Prime Minister of India with whom they reached an agreement to double in five years, i.e. to increase to over 100 billion euros, their trade.
